---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import MedicalDisclaimer from '../../components/MedicalDisclaimer.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Find an MCL Specialist"
  description="Find a hematologist-oncologist with experience treating mantle cell lymphoma. Why specialist care matters and how to find the right doctor."
>
  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-teal-primary/5 via-warm-white to-sage/20">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-charcoal mb-6">Find a Specialist</h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-charcoal/60 leading-relaxed">
        Why specialist experience matters for MCL, and how to find the right care team.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-16 md:py-20 bg-warm-white">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <div class="prose max-w-none">
        <div class="bg-teal-primary/5 rounded-2xl p-8 mb-12 border border-teal-primary/10">
          <p class="text-lg text-charcoal/80 leading-relaxed mb-0">
            Because MCL is rare and treatment is evolving rapidly, we strongly recommend that all patients seek care from — or at minimum, consult with — a hematologist-oncologist who has specific experience treating mantle cell lymphoma.
          </p>
        </div>

        <h2>Why Specialist Care Matters</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70">
          MCL treatment decisions are complex and nuanced. An experienced specialist is more likely to:
        </p>
        <ul class="text-charcoal/70 space-y-2">
          <li>Accurately characterize your specific disease subtype</li>
          <li>Know the latest treatment options and clinical trial opportunities</li>
          <li>Have experience managing the unique side effects and challenges of MCL therapies</li>
          <li>Be connected to a network of MCL-focused researchers and clinicians</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>How to Find a Specialist</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70">
          Here are several ways to connect with MCL-experienced physicians:
        </p>
        <ol class="text-charcoal/70 space-y-4">
          <li>
            <strong>Major Cancer Centers:</strong> NCI-designated comprehensive cancer centers typically have lymphoma specialists with MCL experience. Consider scheduling a consultation, even if your ongoing care happens locally.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Ask your oncologist:</strong> Your current doctor may be able to recommend a colleague with specific MCL expertise for a second opinion.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Clinical trial sites:</strong> Institutions running MCL clinical trials often have the most experienced specialists.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Contact MCLA:</strong> Our team can help point you toward MCL-experienced physicians in your region.
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h2>Questions to Ask a Potential Specialist</h2>
        <ul class="text-charcoal/70 space-y-2">
          <li>How many MCL patients do you currently treat?</li>
          <li>What is your recommended treatment approach for my specific situation?</li>
          <li>Are you involved in MCL research or clinical trials?</li>
          <li>Can you coordinate care with my local oncologist?</li>
          <li>What support services are available at your center?</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Telemedicine Options</h2>
        <p class="text-charcoal/70">
          Many major cancer centers now offer telemedicine consultations, making it easier for patients in remote areas to access expert opinions without traveling. Ask about virtual consultation options when scheduling your appointment.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-sage/30 rounded-xl p-6 my-8">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-charcoal mb-3">Need Help Finding a Specialist?</h3>
          <p class="text-charcoal/70 mb-4">
            Contact our team and we'll help connect you with MCL-experienced physicians in your area.
          </p>
          <a
            href="/contact"
            class="inline-flex items-center px-6 py-2.5 bg-teal-primary text-white font-semibold rounded-lg hover:bg-teal-dark transition-colors no-underline text-sm"
          >
            Contact MCLA
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <MedicalDisclaimer />
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
